  <static seed="45" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring77.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{24t^{5}-12t^{4}+30t^{3}}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>6t^{3}\mathopen{}\left(4t^{2}-2t+5\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The greatest common factor is <m>6t^3</m>, so we can factor the polynomial as follows:</p>
<p><m>{24t^{5}-12t^{4}+30t^{3}}={6t^{3}\mathopen{}\left(4t^{2}-2t+5\right)}</m></p>
</solution>
